Manual Testing Interview Questions
(4–5 Years Experience)


====================================================
SECTION 1: Manual Testing Basics
====================================================
1. What is software testing?
2. What is manual testing?
3. Why is manual testing still important even when automation exists?
4. What is the difference between manual testing and automation testing?
5. What are the objectives of manual testing?
6. What is SDLC and STLC?
7. What is the role of a tester in an Agile team?


====================================================
SECTION 2: Testing Types & Levels
====================================================
8. What are the different levels of testing?
9. What is unit testing?
10. What is integration testing?
11. What is system testing?
12. What is user acceptance testing (UAT)?
13. What is smoke testing?
14. What is sanity testing?
15. Difference between smoke and sanity testing.
16. What is regression testing?
17. When do you perform regression testing?
18. What is exploratory testing?
19. What is ad-hoc testing?


====================================================
SECTION 3: Test Case & Test Scenario
====================================================
20. What is a test case?
21. What are the components of a test case?
22. Difference between test case and test scenario.
23. What is a test plan?
24. What does a test plan include?
25. What is a test strategy?
26. Difference between test plan and test strategy.
27. How do you write effective test cases?
28. What is traceability matrix (RTM)?
29. Why is RTM important?


====================================================
SECTION 4: Defect / Bug Life Cycle
====================================================
30. What is a defect or bug?
31. What is the defect life cycle?
32. What are the different defect statuses?
33. Difference between severity and priority.
34. Who decides defect priority and severity?
35. What is a blocker, critical, major, and minor defect?
36. What information should be included in a defect report?
37. How do you report a defect effectively?


====================================================
SECTION 5: Black Box Testing Techniques
====================================================
38. What is black box testing?
39. What are black box testing techniques?
40. Explain equivalence partitioning.
41. Explain boundary value analysis.
42. Explain decision table testing.
43. Explain state transition testing.
44. Explain use case testing.
45. Which technique do you use most and why?


====================================================
SECTION 6: Agile & Scrum (Very Important)
====================================================
46. What is Agile methodology?
47. What is Scrum?
48. What are Scrum ceremonies?
49. What is a sprint?
50. What is a user story?
51. What is acceptance criteria?
52. What is backlog grooming / refinement?
53. What is a daily stand-up?
54. What is sprint review and sprint retrospective?
55. What is the tester’s role in sprint planning?


====================================================
SECTION 7: Test Execution & Reporting
====================================================
56. How do you execute test cases?
57. What is test execution report?
58. What is test closure?
59. What metrics do you track in testing?
60. What is defect leakage?
61. What is defect density?
62. How do you ensure test coverage?


====================================================
SECTION 8: Scenario-Based Manual Testing Questions
====================================================
63. How would you test a login page manually?
64. How would you test a signup/registration form?
65. How would you test an e-commerce checkout page?
66. What test cases would you write for a search functionality?
67. How do you test a payment gateway?
68. A bug is rejected by the developer. How do you handle it?
69. What do you do if requirements are unclear?
70. How do you test without documentation?


====================================================
SECTION 9: Real Project & Experience-Based Questions
====================================================
71. What domain have you worked on?
72. How do you prioritize test cases when time is limited?
73. How do you handle last-minute changes?
74. How do you ensure quality under tight deadlines?
75. Have you ever missed a bug? What did you learn?
76. How do you collaborate with developers and product owners?


====================================================
SECTION 10: Interview Closing Questions
====================================================
77. What challenges have you faced in manual testing?
78. What is your approach to quality assurance?
79. How do you balance manual and automation testing?
80. How do you mentor junior manual testers?
